--Now I see the pattern clearly. There are TWO major categories of errors:

**Group 1: Module parse failures** - These are "exposed modules" from the plugin that go through `dynamic-module-import-loader` but NOT through `ts-loader`. The loader chain only includes the dynamic-module-import-loader, so TypeScript syntax (enums, type annotations, JSX) fails to parse. This is likely because these files are in `packages/ocs`, `packages/odf`, etc. which need to be matched by the ts-loader include rule.

**Group 2: TypeScript type errors** - PF6 API changes (renamed components, removed props, etc.)

