The loader runs FIRST (pushed last in the array). It passes back TypeScript source. Then ts-loader should run next. But the error says only dynamic-module-import-loader ran.

The problem must be that the ts-loader `include: /packages/` rule doesn't match these specific files. Let me think about why...

The ModuleFederationPlugin `exposes` creates special container modules. When webpack resolves the module for an exposed path like `@odf/core/features`, it goes through `node_modules/@odf/core` (symlink) → `packages/odf/features.ts`. The real resolved path should be `<project>/packages/odf/features.ts`.

